<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_Beginner_GameplayInspiration" s="313988">
  <T n="name">0xD4DF6CC6<!--String: "What Should I Do Next?"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\Beginner\Beginner_GameplayInspiration_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:6db29ab7aa7f6bce</T>
      <T n="text">0x80212B24<!--String: "In The Sims 4, only your <b><font color='#199C2C'>imagination</font></b> sets the limits! But sometimes, with near endless possibilities, it can be hard to know where to start. Let us offer some <b><font color='#199C2C'>suggestions</font></b>!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\Beginner\Beginner_GameplayInspiration_2.png" n="image">2f7d0004:00000000:6db29ab7aa7f6bcd</T>
      <T n="text">0xFD705D61<!--String: "A popular playstyle among Simmers (Sims fans) is playing the <b><font color='#199C2C'>same family, generation after generation</font></b>, and growing an impressive family tree! \n\nHaving babies and nurturing them as they age up to Toddlers, Children, and Teenagers allows you to play with all the different <b><font color='#199C2C'>life stages</font></b>.\n\nDid you know the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Fertile Trait</font></b> from the Reward Store increases your chances of having <b><font color='#199C2C'>twins and triplets</font></b>?"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\Beginner\Beginner_GameplayInspiration_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:6db29ab7aa7f6bcc</T>
      <T n="text">0x794D98F2<!--String: "Why not experiment with how Sims <b><font color='#199C2C'>interact</font></b>, and what impact different <b><font color='#199C2C'>Social Interactions</font></b> have on their relationships? Become the life of the party, an irresistible heartbreaker, or spread chaos wherever you go! \n\nTry one of the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Aspirations</font></b> in the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Love</font></b>, <b><font color='#199C2C'>Popularity</font></b>, or <b><font color='#199C2C'>Deviance</font></b> categories for some inspiration, or work on the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Charisma</font></b>, <b><font color='#199C2C'>Comedy</font></b>, or <b><font color='#199C2C'>Mischief</font></b> Skill to unlock unique interactions.\n\nSims who reach Mischief level 3 can buy a <b><font color='#199C2C'>voodoo doll</font></b> via a computer. Better stay on their good side…"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\Beginner\Beginner_GameplayInspiration_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:6db29ab7aa7f6bcb</T>
      <T n="text">0xFDCA2E45<!--String: "Some Sims want to be the best, maxing out as many <b><font color='#199C2C'>Skills</font></b>, <b><font color='#199C2C'>Careers</font></b>, and <b><font color='#199C2C'>Aspirations</font></b> as they can!\n\nA true <b><font color='#199C2C'>virtuoso</font></b> might work hard to climb the ranks of the Musician branch of the Entertainment Career while leveling every instrument Skill, while a <b><font color='#199C2C'>foodie</font></b> dedicates themselves to the Cooking, Gourmet Cooking, and Mixology Skills as well as the Food Aspirations.\n\nMastering Skills is also a great way to make <b><font color='#199C2C'>Simoleons</font></b>; why not build your fortune creating <b><font color='#199C2C'>masterpieces</font></b> with the Painting Skill or <b><font color='#199C2C'>hacking</font></b> with the Programming Skill?"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\Beginner\Beginner_GameplayInspiration_5.png">2f7d0004:00000000:6db29ab7aa7f6bca</T>
      <T n="text">0x8A942720<!--String: "The world is full of things to discover! <b><font color='#199C2C'>Explore each Neighborhood</font></b> and experience what they have to offer. New places also offer new <b><font color='#199C2C'>Collectibles</font></b> such as harvestable plants, fishes, fossils, and crystals.\n\nWhy not <b><font color='#199C2C'>show off your discoveries</font></b> at home with shelves filled with fossils, aquariums with rare fish, or a flourishing garden with rare (perhaps even <i>supernatural</i>) plants? \n\nSome <b><font color='#199C2C'>secrets</font></b> exist outside the edges of the World Map. If you were to encounter a strange tree or an old mine entrance, perhaps you should take a closer look… "--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\Beginner\Beginner_CreateASim_1.png" n="image">2f7d0004:00000000:550083ef20f89324</T>
      <T n="text">0xF39FB007<!--String: "Explore every facet of <b><font color='#199C2C'>Create a Sim</font></b> and see how far you can push the customization tools! Why not try to create yourself, a friend, a fairytale character, or a celebrity?\n\nWhat kind of character would make for a great <b><font color='#199C2C'>friend</font></b>, <b><font color='#199C2C'>enemy</font></b>, or <b><font color='#199C2C'>love interest</font></b> for your Sim? Create them, add them to your world, and see what happens!\n\n<b><font color='#199C2C'>Media tropes</font></b> can be a great source of inspiration. Who is your version of the gold digger, the nosy neighbor, the hopeless romantic, the secretive hacker, or the evil genius?"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\Beginner\Beginner_GameplayInspiration_7.png">2f7d0004:00000000:6db29ab7aa7f6bc8</T>
      <T n="text">0x2A8494CD<!--String: "Last but not least, let your creative juices flow in <b><font color='#199C2C'>Build Mode</font></b>. Play around with the tools and explore the Object catalog to discover the depth of possibility this game mode has to offer.\n\n<b><font color='#199C2C'>Recreating</font></b> a building you’ve visited or lived in, or a floorplan you found online, can be a fun challenge. You could also <b><font color='#199C2C'>research</font></b> different architectural and interior design styles, and create your own <b><font color='#199C2C'>interpretations</font></b>! \n\n<b><font color='#199C2C'>Leave reality behind</font></b> and pull your inspiration from fairy tales and science fiction; who wouldn’t love to live in a giant mushroom or spaceship?"--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
